# Local-only secrets for scripts that need direct DB / Stripe access.
# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
#
# NEVER commit `.dev.vars` itself — only this `.dev.vars.example`.

SUPABASE_URL=https://wjhdsodlxekvhpahascs.supabase.co

# §2026-05-31 — PRIMARY auth path for scripts/team-chat*.mjs.
# Lets local scripts read/write TeamChat via the Worker admin endpoints
# WITHOUT exposing the Supabase service_role key locally (Worker keeps
# service_role in CF env; this token is a separate, rotatable admin proxy).
#
# Setup ONCE:
#   1. openssl rand -hex 32                          # generate (copy output)
#   2. wrangler secret put CLAUDE_ADMIN_API_TOKEN    # paste same value
#   3. Below: CLAUDE_ADMIN_API_TOKEN=<same value>    # paste again here
#
# After this, scripts/team-chat*.mjs all work via Worker — no service_role.
#
# Worker endpoints unlocked by this token:
#   GET  /api/admin/team-chat/filter?author=&status=&limit=    (read)
#   POST /api/admin/team-chat/send  + X-Admin-Post-As: fei|leon|claude  (write)
#   POST /api/admin/team-chat/set-status                       (status flip)
CLAUDE_ADMIN_API_TOKEN=

# (deprecated — not needed by current scripts; kept here only as reference
# for legacy migrations that might run psql directly via Supabase REST API.
# If you need direct DB access, Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings →
# API → service_role secret.)
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
